2. Booking facility for logged-in users: once users are logged in they need to be able to book a cab for a specified time. This tab should include the following facilities;\par
A location tab has to appear first in which first he should be asked to enter the pickup point and destination.\par
Pickup point: When clicking in this tab, there has be 3 options to select a pickup point;\par
1. Enter Pincode-here user can enter the current pin code and get a list of places with that pin code\par
 2. Type in location-user can enter his pickup point in words.\par
3. Detecting location-a google map icon has to show.When clicking it the system should be able to detect his current location and show him a list.\par
\b Time selection\b0  in which the user should be able to select the time at which he/she needs a cab, specifically asking whether it is AM or PM, a list showing the \b fare\b0  of cab service including the tax, and a \b payment gateway\b0  for users to pay the cash based on the above list. The payment page should have all modes including UPI, Credit card, Debit card, and bank transfer. After payment customer should be shown the \b expected time \b0 of arrival which will be updated by the driver from their profile. The user shall be able to \b track\b0  his cab on google maps also. It should be a live location.\par
3. \b Cancellation\b0 : within 30min of booking user should be able to cancel his booking and a refund should be initiated. A refund initiation message should be sent to the registered mail and mobile number.\par
4. \b Feedback\b0 : after the user has arrived at the targeted location, he should be asked about the experience and feedback of the journey, and also he can rate the driver which will update the score of the driver in his profile.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Rating page: The user shall be able to rate the cab on a scale of 1-10 and write a feedback.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj When a user searches for a cab, the driver with the \cf1 highest score should be shown first in the search suggestions\par
\cf0 5. \b Customer support\b0 : this should be available to all users in which there should be a place for a customer support contact number and an email for sending complaints and suggestions.\par
6. \b Forget password\b0 : if users forget their password they should be able to reset the password, for which an OTP-based password reset facility has to be made.OTP should be sent to the registered mail as well as the mobile number.\par
\ul\par
