2. Login: All registered users should be able to \b log in \b0 by entering their registered mobile/email and their password. If any one of them is wrong then an \b error message \b0 has to be shown indicating that the username or password is wrong. A \b forgot password option \b0 has to be shown for drivers who type their password wrong 2 times. By clicking this he should be able to reset the password based on an OTP-based system which has to be sent to the registered email and mobile number.\par
After successful login, the driver dashboard should include functions like the \b profile of self \b0 which will show all the details the driver had given during the registration, his \b booking history, payment history, and a point table\b0  which is prepared based on the feedback provided by the customer after his journey and on the top right corner he should be shown an option to\b  edit\b0  the information given by him.\par
